Movie: Nick Mullen: The Year of the Dragon
We're All Going to the World's Fair

Review: “In the midst of being as a whole an open place occurs. There is a clearing, a lighting. Thought of in reference to what is, to beings, this clearing is in a greater degree than are beings. This open center is therefore not surrounded by what is; rather, the lighting center itself encircles all that is, like the Nothing which we scarcely know. That which is can only be, as a being, if it stands within and stands out within…
The best Rohmer films capture that feeling of entering someone’s apartment for the first time. The best Rohmer films make you want to put the coffee pot on at 11 pm.
